headlines.description: — LaMelo Ball made a career-high seven 3-pointers and finished with 24 points, 10 assists and seven rebounds, and the Charlotte Hornets defeated the short-handed Houston Rockets 119-94 Monday night for their second straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ball, Hornets use strong 4th quarter to beat Rockets 119-94

headlines.description: — Bradley Beal scored 35 points and the Washington Wizards held on for a rare win, beating the Chicago Bulls 105-101 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beal scores 35, Wizards hold off Bulls 105-101 for rare win

headlines.description: — Fred VanVleet and Pascal Siakam each scored 32 points and the Toronto Raptors put together a second-half rally to beat the Memphis Grizzlies 128-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: VanVleet, Siakam lead Toronto rally to overcome Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Kristaps Porzingis had 27 points, 13 rebounds and six blocks, Luka Doncic scored 26 points and the Dallas Mavericks held off the Minnesota Timberwolves 127-122 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Porzingis, Doncic help Mavericks hold off Wolves, 127-122

events.name: Golden State Warriors at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray had 27 points, 10 rebounds and eight steals, DeMar DeRozan had 21 points and 10 assists, and the San Antonio Spurs beat the Golden State Warriors 105-100 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, DeRozan guide Spurs past Warriors, 105-100

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored a season-high 36 points, Mikal Bridges added 22 and the Phoenix Suns rallied in the fourth quarter to beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 119-113 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores season-high 36, Suns beat Cavs 119-113

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James had 28 points, 14 rebounds and 12 assists for his third triple-double of the season, and the Los Angeles Lakers beat the Oklahoma City Thunder 119-112 in overtime on Monday night to win their fifth in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers rally past Thunder 119-112 in OT for 5th win in a row
